SIMPLE: grindstone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grindstone
<hw>Grind"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A flat, circular
stone, revolving on an axle, for grinding or sharpening tools, or
shaping or smoothing objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To hold one's nose to the grindstone</b></col>,
<col><b>To bring one's nose to the grindstone</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to
oppress one; to keep one in a condition of servitude.</cd> -- <col><b>To
put one's nose to the grindstone</b></col> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>to oppress
one; to cause one to work hard and steadily.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>to
set oneself to a long and arduous task.</cd> -- <col><b>To keep one's
nose to the grindstone</b></col> <cd>to continue at a long and arduous
task; to apply oneself steadily to one's duties.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>They might be ashamed, for lack of courage, to suffer the
Laced⟦ae⟧monians to <qex>hold their noses to the grindstone</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. North.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gringo</ent>⟦br⟧
